        ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Pods
             ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Containers
What is a Node? (Master & Worker)
Node = A machine (VM or physical server)

Runs Linux

Has CPU, RAM, Disk

Can be an EC2 instance

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ Why This Architecture Is Powerful (Theory)
No idle infrastructure
High scalability
Cost-efficient
Cloud-native
Suitable for microservices

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ Interview-Ready Summary (IMPORTANT)

Modern CI/CD systems use event-driven pipelines that create temporary containers or Kubernetes pods to execute builds and tests, 
ensuring zero resource wastage and high scalability.

A pod is the smallest deployable unit in Kubernetes and can contain one or more containers.
Kubernetes uses pods instead of running containers directly because pods provide shared networking and storage, group containers that must work together, and allow Kubernetes to manage container lifecycles efficiently.
This abstraction simplifies scheduling, scaling, and operational management of containers in a cluster.


CI/CD Interview Questions (DevOps)
Foundational / Conceptual
What is CI/CD? Explain in simple terms.
What is the difference between Continuous Integration, Continuous Delivery, and Continuous Deployment?
Why is CI/CD important for software delivery?
What are some common CI/CD tools you have worked with?
What is a pipeline in CI/CD?
What is the difference between a build pipeline and a release pipeline?
Pipeline & Jobs
What is a job or stage in a CI/CD pipeline?
Explain a typical CI/CD pipeline flow from code commit to deployment.
How do you trigger a pipeline automatically? (webhooks, schedule, manual)
How can you ensure your pipeline fails fast if something goes wrong?
How do you handle environment-specific deployments (dev, staging, production)?
Containers & Kubernetes in CI/CD
What is the difference between a CI container and an application container?
What is a pod, and why does Kubernetes use pods for CI/CD?
What is a worker node and what role does it play in CI/CD?
What is a master node (control plane) and what role does it play in CI/CD?
What is a container runtime, and what role does it play in CI/CD pipelines?

Can one pod have multiple containers? If yes, when is it used?
Advanced / Real-World
How do you handle secrets in a CI/CD pipeline?
How do you implement rollback in a CI/CD pipeline?
How can CI/CD pipelines improve team collaboration and code quality?
How do you scale CI/CD pipelines in a large organization?
What is a self-hosted runner? How is it different from a managed runner?
What is the difference between GitHub Actions, Jenkins, GitLab CI, and CircleCI?
How do you integrate automated testing in CI/CD pipelines?
How do you handle zero-downtime deployments?
Scenario-Based / Troubleshooting
Your pipeline fails at the deployment stage. How do you debug it?
A container fails to start in a pod during CI/CD. How do you approach it?
How do you reduce resource wastage in CI/CD pipelines?
How do you ensure your CI/CD pipelines are secure?
How would you design a CI/CD pipeline for a microservices architecture?

